ZH: 他被误解了，鸣冤叫屈。
EN: He was misunderstood and cried foul.

ZH: 她被错误地指控，只能鸣冤叫屈。
EN: She was wrongly accused and had to cry injustice.

ZH: 这是他第三次被冤枉了，他决定要鸣冤叫屈。
EN: This is the third time he has been wronged, he decided to speak out against it.

ZH: 他受到不公正的对待的时候，总是鸣冤叫屈。
EN: He always cries foul when he is treated unfairly.

ZH: 老板错误地解雇了他，他只能鸣冤叫屈。
EN: The boss wrongly fired him, he can only cry injustice.

ZH: 他觉得自己不应该被指控，便开始鸣冤叫屈。
EN: He felt he shouldn't be accused, so he started to speak out against it.

ZH: 在这个不公正的社会里，我们常常需要鸣冤叫屈。
EN: In this unjust society, we often need to cry foul.

ZH: 遭受不公正对待时，我们应该学会鸣冤叫屈。
EN: When treated unfairly, we should learn to speak out against it.

ZH: 小狗被误解了，开始鸣冤叫屈。
EN: The puppy was misunderstood and started to cry injustice.

ZH: 当我的权益受到侵犯时，我会毫不犹豫地鸣冤叫屈。
EN: When my rights are violated, I will not hesitate to cry foul.

ZH: 发现自己被隐瞒了真相，她决定鸣冤叫屈。
EN: Discovering that the truth was hidden from her, she decided to speak out against it.

ZH: 遭受不公正待遇时，不要忍气吞声，要鸣冤叫屈。
EN: When treated unfairly, don't just accept it, speak out against it.

ZH: 没有证据的情况下指控他是不公平的，他决定鸣冤叫屈。
EN: Accusing him without evidence is unfair, so he decided to cry injustice.

ZH: 被无辜关进监狱，他只能鸣冤叫屈。
EN: Innocently locked up in prison, he could only cry foul.

ZH: 面对虚假指控，她坚持鸣冤叫屈。
EN: Faced with false accusations, she persisted in crying injustice.

ZH: 遇到不公正的对待时，我们要勇敢鸣冤叫屈。
EN: When faced with unfair treatment, we must bravely cry foul.

ZH: 受到欺凌时，学会鸣冤叫屈是很重要的。
EN: When being bullied, it is important to learn to speak out against it.

ZH: 遇到不公平事情，我们不能选择沉默，应该鸣冤叫屈。
EN: When faced with unfair situations, we should not choose to remain silent but speak out against it.

ZH: 被谣言围绕时，不要默不作声，要鸣冤叫屈。
EN: When surrounded by rumors, don't stay silent, speak out against it.
